    "timeline_info_wYQpBf": {
      "type": "timeline-Info",
      "blocks": {
        "timeline_Gr4e63": {
          "type": "timeline",
          "settings": {
            "year": "2012",
            "title": "The Pioneer of Mad Honey Trade from Nepal",
            "content": "<p>Our founder, a passionate beekeeper and leader, has always been deeply connected to the wild traditions of honey hunting in Nepal. He loves to travel across the country, meeting local communities and advocating for the unique Mad Honey that was virtually unknown to the world. His vision was to preserve this rare honey and make it known internationally while helping the local honey hunters improve their lives.</p><p>Early days, when Mad Honey was unknown to the world, he worked tirelessly to create a market for Mad Honey and honey-based products, facing many challenges along the way. As a community leader and government representative, he played a key role in supporting the honey-hunting communities, ensuring fair trade and protecting their traditions.</p><p>Today, his dedication continues to inspire the next generation of beekeepers, as he remains committed to supporting local communities and protecting the environment while sharing the unique story of Nepal’s Mad Honey with the world.</p>",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/ceodad.webp"
          }
        },
        "timeline_nMN36d": {
          "type": "timeline",
          "settings": {
            "year": "2016",
            "title": "Founder Medicinal Mad Honey",
            "content": "<p>Inspired by my father, a beekeeper and leader of honey-hunting communities, guided me to the values of resilience, sustainability, and respect for nature. His lifelong dedication to preserving ancient traditions and uplifting local communities supports my inspiration for continuing his legacy.</p><p>Carrying my roots from the Himalayas and resilient honey-hunting communities shaped my philosophy: that the most profound forms of self-care come from the gifts of nature, preserved and shared responsibly.</p><p>My journey began with a simple idea to honour the legacy of the Himalayan honey hunters and bring their rare treasure, Mad Honey, to the world. Along the way, I discovered that this was more than a product; it was a story of resilience, sustainability, and the connection between humanity and the earth.</p><p>Thank you for letting us be a part of this journey!</p>",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/founder.jpg"
          }
        }
      },
      "block_order": [
        "timeline_Gr4e63",
        "timeline_nMN36d"
      ],
