    "timeline_info_BbciWg": {
      "type": "timeline-Info",
      "blocks": {
        "timeline_ztJbmN": {
          "type": "timeline",
          "settings": {
            "year": "2018",
            "title": "Our First Step :",
            "content": "<p>In our early days, limited packaging materials in Nepal led us to start with glass jars and traditional <em>lokhta </em>(Nepali) paper boxes. These materials were recyclable and environmentally friendly, aligning with our values. Beginning with small batches, we utilized locally available resources, laying the foundation for sustainable growth.</p>",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/medicinalmadhooney.webp"
          }
        },
        "timeline_9gqWCF": {
          "type": "timeline",
          "settings": {
            "year": "2020",
            "title": "Our First Evolution",
            "content": "<p>Over two years, we shipped hundreds of jars globally. However, challenges arose as our products travelled thousands of miles damage issues, high shipment weights, and excessive use of bubble wrap and boxes became recurring problems. After thorough research, we transitioned to food-grade PET plastic jars, the most widely recycled type of plastic. This switch significantly reduced shipment weight, fuel consumption, and emissions, making a positive environmental impact.</p>",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/mmhbox.webp"
          }
        },
        "timeline_EcDCgK": {
          "type": "timeline",
          "settings": {
            "year": "2024",
            "title": "One Step Closure to Perfection",
            "content": "<p>By the end of 2024, after thousands of shipments worldwide, we reimagined our packaging to celebrate the stories of honey hunters and their traditions. The new design features exquisite handmade artwork that narrates the journey of honey hunting. Maintaining our branding colours and minimalist design, this packaging embodies our heritage and dedication to storytelling.</p>",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/mmhbox2.webp"
          }
        },
        "timeline_hcnF68": {
          "type": "timeline",
          "settings": {
            "year": "2025 and Beyond",
            "title": "We added more products in our Exotic collection.",
            "content": "<p>A decade of perseverance has brought us remarkable challenges, learnings, and opportunities to innovate. Recognizing the waste of wild honey wax post-extraction, we were inspired by Ayurveda’s insights into its benefits for skin care. This led to the creation of our wild honey lip balms in three flavours and a red mud and mad honey blend soap bar the first skincare product derived from wild mad honey. We continue to research and experiment and hope to launch more natural skin care products in the coming days. In collaboration with honey hunters with over 60 years of expertise and local handicraft artists, we are soon launching a limited Reserve <a href=\"/collections/all\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"mad honey shop\">Mad Honey Collection</a>. These exclusive batches will soon be available after our new spring harvests.</p>",
            "image": "shopify://shop_images/products.jpg"
          }
        }
      },
